1
00:00:02,338 --> 00:00:03,235
Though so.

2
00:00:03,859 --> 00:00:06,020
I know an adventurer when I see one.

3
00:00:07,844 --> 00:00:11,644
A thrilling profession you’ve got
I once hoped to join your ranks.

4
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:14,950
I guess that’s what kids do.

5
00:00:15,292 --> 00:00:17,792
Dream big foolish dreams that always fall flat.

6
00:01:58,783 --> 00:02:01,603
When I was younger, I
played sidekick to a friend

7
00:02:01,627 --> 00:02:04,447
who used to go on all
sorts of little adventures.

8
00:02:05,968 --> 00:02:10,271
Foolhardy and with energy to spare, he was
like a gorilla trapped in the body of a kid.

9
00:02:11,412 --> 00:02:14,634
That said, he was a good kid
who always cared for his friends.

10
00:02:16,516 --> 00:02:20,238
As we grew up, I forgot our
dreams of braving the unknown.

11
00:02:21,980 --> 00:02:25,002
Until he invited me to join his
party and become the real thing.

12
00:02:27,784 --> 00:02:31,625
I wonder how different my life would
be if I'd only taken his hand back then.

13
00:02:34,086 --> 00:02:38,287
It's been ten years now since that
happened, and I regret it to this day.

14
00:02:41,589 --> 00:02:43,829
And why exactly are
you sharing this with me?

15
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:47,510
Well, my village's harvest
festival is coming up.

16
00:02:48,551 --> 00:02:52,752
My brother sent me into the woods to find some
herbs for cooking, which should have been no issue.

17
00:02:53,432 --> 00:02:54,432
But you see...

18
00:02:56,674 --> 00:02:58,835
I fell in a bottomless
swamp and it became one.

19
00:02:59,675 --> 00:03:00,675
Hear me out.

20
00:03:01,016 --> 00:03:03,077
My biggest regret was not taking his hand.

21
00:03:04,037 --> 00:03:07,319
So please, don't let
yours be not taking mine.

22
00:03:07,939 --> 00:03:09,660
You have a chance to change my fate here.

23
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:12,321
Just give me a moment.

24
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:13,901
I need to think.

25
00:03:14,342 --> 00:03:15,342
Huh?

26
00:03:15,442 --> 00:03:16,442
You're messing with me.

27
00:03:16,783 --> 00:03:18,844
What's so confusing it
requires that much thought?

28
00:03:18,964 --> 00:03:20,584
Your hand is dirty.

29
00:03:20,945 --> 00:03:22,205
I'm gonna drown in this muck.

30
00:03:22,345 --> 00:03:24,206
You can wash your
hands off later, can't you?

31
00:03:25,507 --> 00:03:26,507
And besides, miss,

32
00:03:27,977 --> 00:03:28,978
To a certain extent.

33
00:03:29,979 --> 00:03:31,540
We grown-ups are dirty by nature.

34
00:03:32,261 --> 00:03:33,261
Please.

35
00:03:33,662 --> 00:03:36,484
I've met countless adults,
but none quite as filthy as you.

36
00:03:36,964 --> 00:03:38,522
I must ask you for more time.

37
00:03:38,546 --> 00:03:42,489
If you would let me think, I
might recall this belt to pull you out.

38
00:03:42,989 --> 00:03:43,410
Got it.

39
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,471
But could we pick up the pace a bit?

40
00:03:45,872 --> 00:03:46,873
Let me see...

41
00:03:47,813 --> 00:03:51,056
Mistress Frieren, did you
have any luck finding herbs?

42
00:03:51,336 --> 00:03:52,717
Oh, I remember.

43
00:03:59,624 --> 00:04:00,904
I can take it from here, thanks.

44
00:04:01,005 --> 00:04:02,006
You're so welcome.

45
00:04:02,346 --> 00:04:04,188
Sorry for the trouble my mistress caused.

46
00:04:04,408 --> 00:04:06,090
Hey, I'm in no spot to complain.

47
00:04:06,570 --> 00:04:07,851
Your friend there saved my life.

48
00:04:08,171 --> 00:04:11,754
Perhaps, but regardless,
I will scold her later.

49
00:04:12,415 --> 00:04:13,415
My night off.

50
00:04:14,256 --> 00:04:17,096
Are you folks sure you don't need
to stop by the village before you go?

51
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:20,942
We're busy preparing for the festival, but
I'd like to find some way to say thanks.

52
00:04:21,723 --> 00:04:23,624
We're hoping to reach a larger town today.

53
00:04:24,325 --> 00:04:26,767
Our supplies are low, so we
need a good place to restock.

54
00:04:27,307 --> 00:04:28,307
Understood.

55
00:04:28,451 --> 00:04:29,872
Well, in that case, be careful.

56
00:04:30,452 --> 00:04:33,412
There are a lot of dangerous, venomous
creatures out there in those woods.

57
00:04:34,513 --> 00:04:35,130
Good to know.

58
00:04:45,554 --> 00:04:47,454
Hey, something just bit me.

59
00:04:47,498 --> 00:04:47,779
What?

60
00:04:48,399 --> 00:04:49,495
You have to be kidding.

61
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:53,181
We were told to be on the lookout for
that sort of danger mere moments ago.

62
00:04:53,441 --> 00:04:55,522
First things first, let's
bandage the wound.

63
00:04:57,675 --> 00:04:59,155
My nose might be bleeding a little.

64
00:05:01,923 --> 00:05:06,445
Any spell that has to do with identifying poison
falls into a priest's realm, so I'm no help.

65
00:05:06,906 --> 00:05:10,908
I don't recognize this reaction, so the
antidotes we have might not do the job.

66
00:05:11,488 --> 00:05:13,449
We should get you checked
at a church to be safe.

67
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:17,712
Now, Fern, for how much longer
can you use your flying magic?

68
00:05:18,012 --> 00:05:21,734
I would say we only have about 30
minutes, since it consumes a lot of mana.

69
00:05:22,214 --> 00:05:24,775
Unfortunately, that won't
get us all the way to the town.

70
00:05:25,316 --> 00:05:26,916
We'll have to head back to that village.

71
00:05:27,457 --> 00:05:28,958
Leave moving the patient to me.

72
00:05:29,378 --> 00:05:30,799
It's really not that big a deal.

73
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,841
I'm going to be fine, trust me.

74
00:05:33,462 --> 00:05:36,662
My master taught me that the best way
to beat poisons is to just tough them out.

75
00:05:37,386 --> 00:05:43,132
Come to think of it, I have seen Eisen take several
poison-coated arrows to the back and be fine.

76
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:45,551
It was enough to knock out a dragon.

77
00:05:45,575 --> 00:05:47,717
Heiter was appalled.

78
00:05:48,675 --> 00:05:49,315
You get it?

79
00:05:49,595 --> 00:05:49,876
No.

80
00:05:50,356 --> 00:05:54,198
The only thing that tale proves is
Mr. Eisen is very far from normal.

81
00:05:54,678 --> 00:06:01,121
What's more, Master Heiter would always remind me,
poison's the cause of 20% of adventurer deaths.

82
00:06:02,202 --> 00:06:03,202
We should hurry.

83
00:06:05,343 --> 00:06:06,039
Why?

84
00:06:06,063 --> 00:06:07,904
This is complete overkill.

85
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:15,131
I'm afraid you're too late.

86
00:06:15,831 --> 00:06:18,052
A few hours from now,
his brain will start to melt.

87
00:06:18,572 --> 00:06:20,473
At that point, it will flow from his nose.

88
00:06:21,453 --> 00:06:22,309
And then he'll die!

89
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:24,070
That's terrifying!

90
00:06:24,094 --> 00:06:25,735
Please guide us, Father.

91
00:06:25,775 --> 00:06:27,455
There must be something we can do for him.

92
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:31,917
That bite was deadly, and could typically
only be cured if treated immediately.

93
00:06:32,637 --> 00:06:34,557
But perhaps my brother
will be able to help you.

94
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:36,514
There you are.

95
00:06:36,754 --> 00:06:37,835
We have a problem, brother.

96
00:06:38,455 --> 00:06:40,636
We both agree this new
tub is too small, right?

97
00:06:40,976 --> 00:06:42,156
There's honor in poverty.

98
00:06:42,756 --> 00:06:43,977
Sure, to a point, maybe.

99
00:06:44,757 --> 00:06:48,158
But impoverishing down to a
tub fit for fingertips seems extreme.

100
00:06:48,998 --> 00:06:50,379
We have greater concerns.

101
00:06:50,939 --> 00:06:52,519
Take a look at this boy for me, Sein.

102
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,080
Hold on.

103
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:56,521
These are the adventurers
I was telling you about.

104
00:06:57,261 --> 00:06:58,661
They're the folks who rescued me.

105
00:07:00,882 --> 00:07:01,882
Look at you.

106
00:07:02,203 --> 00:07:03,503
You were bitten by a snake, huh?

107
00:07:04,427 --> 00:07:05,808
Glad you took my warning to heart.

108
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:12,930
There.

109
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:14,311
Consider my debt repaid.

110
00:07:15,251 --> 00:07:16,251
So long.

111
00:07:16,292 --> 00:07:17,792
I'm going to help out at the plaza.

112
00:07:18,613 --> 00:07:19,613
All right.

113
00:07:21,514 --> 00:07:22,514
I'm not bleeding.

114
00:07:23,274 --> 00:07:24,274
And there's no brains.

115
00:07:25,595 --> 00:07:27,496
Seems the effects of the poison are gone.

116
00:07:30,717 --> 00:07:32,378
Tell me, Father, is he...

117
00:07:33,755 --> 00:07:36,956
He's my little brother,
and quite the priest.

118
00:07:40,117 --> 00:07:43,287
That holy symbol around
your neck, it's awarded to the

119
00:07:43,311 --> 00:07:46,480
most outstanding priest in
a region by the Holy Capital.

120
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:52,742
Your brother came in and instantly cured a poison
a top-level healing expert called Incurable.

121
00:07:54,362 --> 00:07:55,923
He's no less than a genius.

122
00:07:56,823 --> 00:07:59,644
I had a feeling you of all people
would notice, Miss Frieren.

123
00:08:00,164 --> 00:08:01,745
I didn't realize you knew who I was.

124
00:08:02,277 --> 00:08:04,957
Mr. Heiter told me many a story about you.

125
00:08:06,898 --> 00:08:07,898
He's who gave me this.

126
00:08:08,438 --> 00:08:12,939
He came from the capital to observe us, and
I suppose he thought I was doing rather well.

127
00:08:13,939 --> 00:08:17,380
However, I'm still just a
provincial priest in a small village.

128
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,080
This medallion is my greatest achievement.

129
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:25,701
And while I'm very proud, the truth is,
my ability doesn't even compare to Sein's.

130
00:08:26,861 --> 00:08:28,282
You see, we lost our parents.

131
00:08:28,682 --> 00:08:30,162
He was just a child when it happened.

132
00:08:31,502 --> 00:08:35,365
Though I was young myself when
they passed away, I raised my brother.

133
00:08:36,846 --> 00:08:41,050
When he was little, he would often talk
about becoming an adventurer someday.

134
00:08:42,551 --> 00:08:45,912
He didn't want to grow up to be an
ordinary village priest because he

135
00:08:45,936 --> 00:08:49,297
couldn't bear for all his days to
look the same, the way that mine do.

136
00:08:50,698 --> 00:08:53,600
He would tell me that with
eyes full of hopes and dreams.

137
00:08:55,081 --> 00:08:59,145
That shine has dimmed now, as he
becomes more like me each passing year.

138
00:09:00,243 --> 00:09:02,184
His soul is aching for something greater.

139
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:08,548
So please, take my brother with you on
your journey and away from this village.

140
00:09:09,148 --> 00:09:09,769
It's perfect.

141
00:09:10,009 --> 00:09:11,230
You clearly need a priest.

142
00:09:11,650 --> 00:09:14,672
And I'm certain he needs
someone to give him that final push.

143
00:09:18,114 --> 00:09:19,094
Come on, Frieren.

144
00:09:19,134 --> 00:09:20,235
He's an easy yes.

145
00:09:21,015 --> 00:09:21,952
The man's a genius.

146
00:09:21,976 --> 00:09:23,136
What is there to think about?

147
00:09:24,838 --> 00:09:28,360
Whatever it is, it can't be worth risking
my brains coming out of my nose again.

148
00:09:29,345 --> 00:09:33,468
He would make things safer, and our journey's
headed deeper into the unknown from here.

149
00:09:34,368 --> 00:09:36,790
Why are you acting so
wary, Mistress Frieren?

150
00:09:39,092 --> 00:09:41,894
An aversion to my own kind, I suppose.

151
00:09:42,214 --> 00:09:44,134
Yeah, I don't know what
that's supposed to mean.

152
00:09:45,216 --> 00:09:45,672
I don't care.

153
00:09:45,696 --> 00:09:47,697
I'm inviting him whether you like it or not.

154
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:52,620
Where's he going?

155
00:09:52,941 --> 00:09:54,262
Maybe the bar downstairs?

156
00:09:54,702 --> 00:09:57,164
I get the feeling Mr. Sein
spends a lot of time there.

157
00:09:58,205 --> 00:09:59,205
Of course.

158
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:03,059
Alcohol.

159
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Tobacco.

160
00:10:06,260 --> 00:10:07,260
Gambling.

161
00:10:09,661 --> 00:10:11,842
So, at what point does
Corrupt become Depraved?

162
00:10:12,442 --> 00:10:14,203
I'm just getting to know my fellow man.

163
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:16,124
Care to join us, kid?

164
00:10:17,124 --> 00:10:18,124
The name is Stark.

165
00:10:19,084 --> 00:10:20,865
And I came to ask you to join us.

166
00:10:21,725 --> 00:10:22,966
We are looking for a priest.

167
00:10:24,406 --> 00:10:25,527
That's a funny joke.

168
00:10:26,227 --> 00:10:28,207
But I'm already a priest for the village.

169
00:10:28,968 --> 00:10:30,148
I can't go adventuring.

170
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:34,796
Wait, this could be fun.

171
00:10:36,716 --> 00:10:37,836
Take a load off, Stark.

172
00:10:38,556 --> 00:10:40,937
If you can beat me at a
hand, I'll join your party.

173
00:10:40,997 --> 00:10:41,997
Are you for real?

174
00:10:42,197 --> 00:10:43,697
Man of the cloth and my word.

175
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,637
Please don't do it!

176
00:10:50,639 --> 00:10:54,560
Miss Frieren, I think I just heard
Mr. Stark yell from downstairs.

177
00:11:04,362 --> 00:11:06,083
It looks like someone robbed him blind.

178
00:11:06,683 --> 00:11:07,499
How awful.

179
00:11:07,523 --> 00:11:09,220
Who would do such a thing?

180
00:11:09,244 --> 00:11:10,945
No hard feelings.

181
00:11:13,186 --> 00:11:16,187
We grown-ups are dirty,
and we play dirty, too.

182
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:18,784
Someone's robbed him blind, too.

183
00:11:18,808 --> 00:11:21,049
That someone would be the village chief.

184
00:11:21,249 --> 00:11:23,330
A tyrant's got lady luck on a leech.

185
00:11:23,970 --> 00:11:24,970
Sein.

186
00:11:25,491 --> 00:11:27,111
I hear that you're looking for a priest.

187
00:11:27,691 --> 00:11:28,691
Look elsewhere.

188
00:11:29,572 --> 00:11:31,553
You want to become
an adventurer, don't you?

189
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:34,529
There's a massive difference
between want and wanted.

190
00:11:35,189 --> 00:11:36,349
It's too late for me now.

191
00:11:36,889 --> 00:11:40,371
See, I should have left when there was
a chance I could have actually found him.

192
00:11:41,791 --> 00:11:45,252
And if that's not enough, now I
don't even have the wardrobe for it.

193
00:11:48,693 --> 00:11:51,174
Frieren, defeat the Demon King.

194
00:11:51,394 --> 00:11:52,394
Join our party.

195
00:11:52,834 --> 00:11:53,835
It's too late for me.

196
00:11:55,015 --> 00:11:58,156
It's been over 500 years now
since I last fought a demon.

197
00:11:59,196 --> 00:12:01,257
Their battles I've long
forgotten how to win.

198
00:12:02,935 --> 00:12:05,456
I deferred that decision
for centuries too long.

199
00:12:06,556 --> 00:12:09,437
I missed the moment this adventure
would have made sense for me.

200
00:12:10,857 --> 00:12:13,698
Probably because I was
far too cowardly to face him.

201
00:12:15,138 --> 00:12:16,778
None of that matters, Frieren.

202
00:12:18,259 --> 00:12:20,479
Don't dwell on the past
when you have the present.

203
00:12:27,761 --> 00:12:31,482
Find someone else.

204
00:12:32,612 --> 00:12:34,233
You don't have any idea how I feel.

205
00:12:35,134 --> 00:12:36,134
Please.

206
00:12:36,355 --> 00:12:37,656
Your reaction tells me.

207
00:12:38,456 --> 00:12:40,698
And frankly, I couldn't like you less, Sein.

208
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,380
Great.

209
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,177
Well, in that case...

210
00:12:45,201 --> 00:12:47,819
So I've decided you're going
to join us no matter what.

211
00:12:47,843 --> 00:12:49,504
Huh?

212
00:12:50,385 --> 00:12:51,385
But why?

213
00:12:52,927 --> 00:12:55,148
That makes so little sense, it's scary.

214
00:12:56,229 --> 00:12:57,229
You saved me.

215
00:12:57,810 --> 00:12:58,810
So toasty.

216
00:13:00,752 --> 00:13:03,213
I'm truly sorry for all the
trouble that we caused you.

217
00:13:03,874 --> 00:13:04,874
Please excuse us.

218
00:13:07,436 --> 00:13:09,557
How much did it cost
to get everything back?

219
00:13:10,037 --> 00:13:12,978
He said we should take our time
and enjoy the Harvest Festival.

220
00:13:13,719 --> 00:13:15,560
Then he gave it all back to me for free.

221
00:13:15,860 --> 00:13:16,860
A nice man.

222
00:13:16,961 --> 00:13:17,961
It's your lucky day.

223
00:13:18,481 --> 00:13:20,382
He said he didn't know
what to do with the axe.

224
00:13:20,723 --> 00:13:21,723
That's kinda sad.

225
00:13:22,744 --> 00:13:23,764
Here, Mr. Stark.

226
00:13:24,024 --> 00:13:25,024
Put these on.

227
00:13:25,565 --> 00:13:26,386
How rude!

228
00:13:26,486 --> 00:13:29,246
You have to hold them like they're
too gross for your precious hands!

229
00:13:29,385 --> 00:13:31,306
I believe these are yours, Mr. Sein.

230
00:13:33,168 --> 00:13:36,870
Well, hell, someone's grumpy.

231
00:13:36,990 --> 00:13:38,251
What'd I do to set her off?

232
00:13:39,352 --> 00:13:42,214
For starters, you robbed poor
Stark of all his possessions.

233
00:13:43,595 --> 00:13:44,851
I told you that wasn't me.

234
00:13:44,875 --> 00:13:45,875
It was the Chief.

235
00:13:47,417 --> 00:13:49,739
People who gamble
are the lowest of the low.

236
00:13:50,419 --> 00:13:51,039
I get it.

237
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,120
I'm sorry.

238
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:54,702
And to think, that man's
supposed to be a priest.

239
00:13:55,422 --> 00:13:57,664
Any priest who drinks is wrong in my book.

240
00:13:58,249 --> 00:14:03,191
But Mistress Frieren, a priest once told
me that alcohol is the very best medicine.

241
00:14:03,651 --> 00:14:06,193
How dare Heiter poison your young mind?

242
00:14:07,693 --> 00:14:10,633
Regardless of whether he
decides to come with us or

243
00:14:10,657 --> 00:14:13,596
not, I do feel that Sein
should become an adventurer.

244
00:14:14,036 --> 00:14:16,577
That idea has really grown
on you since this all began.

245
00:14:18,078 --> 00:14:21,008
I realized that it might be
nice to give someone the

246
00:14:21,032 --> 00:14:23,961
push they need, just like
Himmel the Hero gave to me.

247
00:14:29,164 --> 00:14:31,946
For whatever reason, the
adventurers decided to hang around.

248
00:14:32,786 --> 00:14:35,467
Their presence has taken
up more than a bit of space.

249
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:43,512
They've been trying to recruit
me every day since their arrival.

250
00:14:47,394 --> 00:14:49,375
I've tried my best to make them stop.

251
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,706
But my efforts have been in vain.

252
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:57,152
They invite me on adventures with cheer in
their voices and eyes full of hopes and dreams.

253
00:14:58,272 --> 00:14:59,392
Like he did back then.

254
00:15:00,913 --> 00:15:03,433
The plan is to travel around
the Northern Lands for a bit.

255
00:15:05,034 --> 00:15:07,174
I'll be back around the
harvest three years from now.

256
00:15:08,154 --> 00:15:10,955
If you aren't ready to hit the
road yet, you can join me then.

257
00:15:12,296 --> 00:15:13,916
Let's go on our next adventure together.

258
00:15:16,767 --> 00:15:20,767
Every time they try to recruit
me, I wonder, why now?

259
00:15:20,791 --> 00:15:25,655
They radiate hope, too
bright for my tired eyes.

260
00:15:27,497 --> 00:15:29,218
You want to know what Sein likes?

261
00:15:29,779 --> 00:15:30,779
For what?

262
00:15:30,860 --> 00:15:34,263
We can't seem to win him
over, so we're looking for ideas.

263
00:15:34,643 --> 00:15:36,064
What does my brother like?

264
00:15:36,464 --> 00:15:39,067
Alcohol, tobacco, and gambling
always seem to attract him.

265
00:15:39,387 --> 00:15:40,608
We've gathered that much.

266
00:15:40,968 --> 00:15:42,470
We're sure this guy's a priest?

267
00:15:43,137 --> 00:15:44,819
Master Heiter was in good company.

268
00:15:45,079 --> 00:15:46,700
All serious priests like to drink.

269
00:15:48,021 --> 00:15:50,323
I'm not sure that I've
met a serious priest.

270
00:15:50,764 --> 00:15:55,048
Let me see... What he adores
more than anything is older women.

271
00:15:55,348 --> 00:15:57,089
How fitting of our depraved priest.

272
00:15:57,450 --> 00:15:58,791
Older ladies, huh?

273
00:15:59,051 --> 00:16:00,051
Thank you.

274
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:03,075
But I'm not entirely sure what
to do with that information.

275
00:16:05,196 --> 00:16:06,196
Hm?

276
00:16:06,317 --> 00:16:07,317
Hello?

277
00:16:09,242 --> 00:16:10,242
Ah, that's right.

278
00:16:10,323 --> 00:16:11,323
You're kidding me.

279
00:16:11,544 --> 00:16:13,925
This sickle is too small
to use, don't you think?

280
00:16:14,506 --> 00:16:15,787
It can hardly cut grass.

281
00:16:16,507 --> 00:16:18,569
Oh, it's you three again.

282
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:22,430
Do you have a minute, Sein?

283
00:16:22,871 --> 00:16:23,872
You're still here.

284
00:16:24,212 --> 00:16:25,433
Come on.

285
00:16:25,773 --> 00:16:27,675
I'm getting sick of repeating myself, kid.

286
00:16:28,135 --> 00:16:29,156
Find someone else.

287
00:16:30,757 --> 00:16:35,060
Say, Sein, wouldn't you like to
travel with an older lady on your arm?

288
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,000
Look at who you're talking to.

289
00:16:37,954 --> 00:16:42,236
The thought of that very scenario was why I
wanted to be an adventurer in the first place.

290
00:16:42,837 --> 00:16:43,577
What a motive.

291
00:16:43,857 --> 00:16:45,018
I'm on the edge of my seat.

292
00:16:45,878 --> 00:16:47,699
Where is this vixen of which you speak?

293
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:50,020
You've been looking right at her, Sein.

294
00:16:51,101 --> 00:16:52,462
Did you realize I'm an elf?

295
00:16:52,802 --> 00:16:55,603
As far as older women go,
I'm as old as you can get.

296
00:16:57,764 --> 00:16:58,925
I knew you were an elf.

297
00:16:59,165 --> 00:17:00,626
I think my brother mentioned that.

298
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:03,367
Ugh.

299
00:17:05,405 --> 00:17:06,405
You're too cruel.

300
00:17:06,726 --> 00:17:08,847
She hardly looks like a
woman, let alone older.

301
00:17:09,187 --> 00:17:10,588
He seems so distressed.

302
00:17:11,329 --> 00:17:12,329
I apologize.

303
00:17:13,290 --> 00:17:16,452
I had no desire to take it to this
level, but you leave me no choice.

304
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:23,056
The time has come to use the ancient
seduction technique taught to me by my master.

305
00:17:31,301 --> 00:17:32,301
What was that?

306
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,002
I blew you a kiss, of course.

307
00:17:35,482 --> 00:17:37,685
Maybe you're too young
to appreciate it, Sonny.

308
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:41,169
Somebody take this twisted child home.

309
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:43,332
That was way too steamy for me.

310
00:17:43,412 --> 00:17:44,773
What's the deal with you two?

311
00:17:45,394 --> 00:17:46,394
That's odd.

312
00:17:46,595 --> 00:17:49,979
When I tried the very same maneuver
on Himmel, it knocked him out cold.

313
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:54,967
Himmel!

314
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:56,467
You are a wicked woman.

315
00:17:57,675 --> 00:17:58,675
How bizarre.

316
00:17:58,896 --> 00:17:59,896
I'm with you.

317
00:18:00,377 --> 00:18:03,478
If I had been the target of your attack,
I would have been in grave danger.

318
00:18:03,658 --> 00:18:07,120
As depraved as he is, he's still
a holy man and a formidable foe.

319
00:18:07,321 --> 00:18:08,581
That's enough already!

320
00:18:09,762 --> 00:18:12,103
I'm not becoming an adventurer, so quit.

321
00:18:12,964 --> 00:18:15,225
But I thought that you
wanted to go after your friend.

322
00:18:16,986 --> 00:18:18,567
You understand my reason, brother.

323
00:18:19,948 --> 00:18:20,948
Do I, Sein?

324
00:18:21,929 --> 00:18:24,450
He promised me that he would
be back here in three years.

325
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,052
He hasn't been back for ten.

326
00:18:28,789 --> 00:18:31,131
The obvious explanation is that he's dead.

327
00:18:34,394 --> 00:18:36,977
So you're going to give up
without ever going to look for him?

328
00:18:39,339 --> 00:18:41,201
Ten years isn't as long as you think.

329
00:18:41,922 --> 00:18:45,285
The more time that you wait, the
greater and greater that number will grow.

330
00:18:46,266 --> 00:18:48,946
You'll wonder if you could have
made it if you'd left town with us.

331
00:18:51,050 --> 00:18:53,913
It's too... Too late, you suppose, correct?

332
00:18:56,248 --> 00:18:58,670
Don't dwell in the past
when you have the present.

333
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:00,510
Sein.

334
00:19:05,514 --> 00:19:06,514
I can't go.

335
00:19:06,995 --> 00:19:08,075
Couldn't then, can't now.

336
00:19:08,596 --> 00:19:10,877
It's been ten years and I
still have the same reason.

337
00:19:12,098 --> 00:19:14,459
It's not so much that I
would miss this village.

338
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,061
I can't leave my brother behind.

339
00:19:17,841 --> 00:19:19,202
You're scared of leaving me?

340
00:19:19,542 --> 00:19:20,542
Why is that?

341
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:26,071
When Mr. Heiter came to observe
us years ago, I heard you both talking.

342
00:19:28,312 --> 00:19:30,053
Your talent could take you far, my lad.

343
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:33,274
There's no doubt you could
serve as a priest in the Holy Capital.

344
00:19:33,634 --> 00:19:33,914
Me?

345
00:19:34,174 --> 00:19:35,194
In the Holy Capital?

346
00:19:36,135 --> 00:19:38,015
Yes, without question.

347
00:19:38,495 --> 00:19:42,497
That sounds great, but what would happen
to my little brother if I chose to go?

348
00:19:43,517 --> 00:19:44,817
He'd come with you, of course.

349
00:19:46,358 --> 00:19:47,358
Understood.

350
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:52,075
Mr. Heiter, I deeply appreciate the offer.

351
00:19:52,995 --> 00:19:54,636
But my life here is just fine.

352
00:19:54,797 --> 00:19:56,618
More than that, it's what my brother knows.

353
00:19:57,418 --> 00:20:00,060
We tragically lost our parents
when he was young, you see.

354
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:02,841
This village is his home.

355
00:20:04,242 --> 00:20:07,724
I do thank you, but I can't take
away the one comfort he has left.

356
00:20:11,606 --> 00:20:12,606
Very well.

357
00:20:14,328 --> 00:20:15,909
You're in a tricky situation.

358
00:20:16,742 --> 00:20:19,283
I suppose I wasted my time by coming here.

359
00:20:19,824 --> 00:20:24,086
But if I'm already wasting time,
perhaps I'll talk with your brother.

360
00:20:24,366 --> 00:20:27,788
The little ones always get a kick
hearing the tales of my adventures.

361
00:20:29,128 --> 00:20:32,030
My brother had a chance to leave
this village, but he stayed for me.

362
00:20:34,611 --> 00:20:37,713
Sein, is that the reason
you've made yourself miserable?

363
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:43,388
You must see that you
and I are not the same.

364
00:20:44,089 --> 00:20:47,634
The decision to stay was mine to make
and I have never in my life regretted it.

365
00:20:48,355 --> 00:20:49,997
Don't pretend that you can say as much.

366
00:20:50,618 --> 00:20:52,581
How long do you intend
to regret your choice?

367
00:20:53,702 --> 00:20:54,702
For shame.

368
00:21:11,217 --> 00:21:12,638
I apologize to my brother.

369
00:21:13,899 --> 00:21:14,899
Good.

370
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:17,601
Please don't get the
wrong idea about the man.

371
00:21:18,461 --> 00:21:19,522
He's kind as can be.

372
00:21:20,623 --> 00:21:22,624
He's never once laid a hand on me before.

373
00:21:24,025 --> 00:21:26,406
It just shows how
strongly he feels about this.

374
00:21:27,387 --> 00:21:29,548
I mean, I'd never seen
that expression on his face.

375
00:21:34,291 --> 00:21:36,232
Well, Frieren, you won.

376
00:21:36,793 --> 00:21:38,454
I'm going to become an adventurer.

377
00:21:39,374 --> 00:21:40,374
My friend might need me.

378
00:21:42,102 --> 00:21:43,883
Ten years isn't as long as you think.

379
00:21:45,123 --> 00:21:46,123
Well, but...

380
00:21:51,705 --> 00:21:53,226
Looking for him is my main goal.

381
00:21:53,666 --> 00:21:54,946
He's the reason I'm doing this.

382
00:21:56,307 --> 00:22:00,788
I'll find that ape and make our
ridiculous childhood dreams come true.

383
00:22:01,969 --> 00:22:05,750
I'll travel with you for now,
but hopefully I'll find him soon.

384
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:08,310
Take that, fish!

385
00:22:08,451 --> 00:22:09,451
I'm impressed.

386
00:22:25,442 --> 00:22:28,584
Maybe I should have asked this
before, but where are you headed?

387
00:22:29,404 --> 00:22:30,404
Heaven, of course.

388
00:22:30,925 --> 00:22:32,826
Is that someplace you
need to work to get to?

389
00:22:33,587 --> 00:22:35,108
Well, I'll end up there when we die.

390
00:22:35,848 --> 00:22:37,629
Even you'll end up there, Mr. Sein?

391
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:39,730
My, what a start.

392
00:22:39,991 --> 00:22:41,711
She doesn't beat around the bush, does she?

393
00:22:42,372 --> 00:22:44,052
Hey, at least you're in it with me, buddy.

394
00:22:45,814 --> 00:22:46,875
Good luck to us both.

